In cocos/network/HttpClient-apple.mm line 174-177:

```
    if ([requestType isEqual: @"PUT"])
    {
        [nsrequest setValue: @"application/x-www-form-urlencoded" forHTTPHeaderField: @"Content-Type"];
    }
```

These codes set "Content-Type" for all "PUT" request, and I can't even override it. Maybe these code should test whether the headers set by user contains custom "Content-Type" first.

The temporary search path was inserted into the begin of the array, but the last element was removed from the array when operation finished.

https://github.com/cocos2d/cocos2d-x/blob/v3/tools/simulator/libsimulator/lib/runtime/ConfigParser.cpp

``` c++
void ConfigParser::readConfig(const string &filepath)
{
    ...
    // add writable path to search path temporarily for reading config file
    vector<std::string> searchPathArray = FileUtils::getInstance()->getSearchPaths();
    searchPathArray.insert(searchPathArray.begin(), FileServer::getShareInstance()->getWritePath());
    FileUtils::getInstance()->setSearchPaths(searchPathArray);
    ...
    // revert search path
    searchPathArray.erase(searchPathArray.end() - 1);
    FileUtils::getInstance()->setSearchPaths(searchPathArray);
    ...
}
```

Notice, the code `searchPathArray.erase(searchPathArray.end() - 1);` means to erase the last element.
